I think we may relax full path for `uname`. Otherwise, it would just make brew unrunable for certain Linux distro.

Alternatively, we could do something like:
```bash
uname()
{
   [[ -x "/usr/bin/uname" ]] && { /usr/bin/uname "$@"; return; }
   [[ -x "/bin/uname" ]] && { /bin/uname "$@"; return;  }
   odie "..."
}
```

